## 10. Lasso Regression

### Why?
Lasso uses an L1 penalty which **zeros out** irrelevant features вҖ” automatic feature selection.

### Objective

$$J_{\text{lasso}} = \|\mathbf{y} - \mathbf{X}\boldsymbol{\beta}\|^2 + \lambda\|\boldsymbol{\beta}\|_1$$

No closed form вҖ” solved with **coordinate descent** using the soft-threshold update:

$$\hat{\beta}_j \leftarrow \text{sign}(z_j)\,\max(|z_j| - \tau,\; 0)$$

where $z_j$ is the simple OLS estimate for $\beta_j$ given all other coefficients fixed.

> The $\max(\cdot, 0)$ is what creates **exact zeros** вҖ” if the signal is weaker than the penalty, the coefficient is killed entirely.

### Key Properties

| | Lasso |
|---|---|
| Sparsity | вң… Exact zeros вҖ” built-in feature selection |
| Closed form | вқҢ No |
| Best for | Many irrelevant features, high-dimensional data |
| Hyperparameter | $\lambda$ |

